Abstract

A commutative associative algebra A ùê¥ italic-A A over ‚ÑÇ ‚ÑÇ blackboard-C {\mathbb{C}} with a derivation is one of the simplest examples of a vertex algebra. However, the differences between the modules for A ùê¥ italic-A A as a vertex algebra and the modules for A ùê¥ italic-A A as an associative algebra are not well understood.

In this paper, I give the classification of finite-dimensional indecomposable untwisted or twisted modules for the polynomial ring in one variable over ‚ÑÇ ‚ÑÇ blackboard-C {\mathbb{C}} as a vertex algebra.
